                            <comment id="14516361" author="ndimiduk" created="Tue, 28 Apr 2015 04:56:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have ProcV2 on master, branch-1, and branch-1.1, so I&apos;m dropping those fix versions. Please add back 1.1.1 if I got that wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14612392" author="enis" created="Thu, 2 Jul 2015 19:09:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We already load the Region Split Policy class in sanity checking for the table description in alter table in all 0.98+ branches:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; void checkClassLoading(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; Configuration conf, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; HTableDescriptor htd)
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
    RegionSplitPolicy.getSplitPolicyClass(htd, conf);
    RegionCoprocessorHost.testTableCoprocessorAttrs(conf, htd);
  }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Resolving this as not a problem. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14724200" author="enis" created="Mon, 31 Aug 2015 22:39:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this issue after 1.0.2 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
